# BodaSure Engineering Standards

## Repository Path Truth (Do Not Guess)

- Entity schemas: `base44/entities/*.jsonc` (31 schemas)
- Backend functions: `base44/functions/*/entry.ts` (40 handlers)
- Frontend SDK: `src/api/base44Client.js` only — never instantiate a second client
- No `src/entities/` or `src/functions/` — backend lives only under `base44/`

## Scale Rules (1M+ Users)

- No query loops inside React components (N+1 ban).
- Lists and dashboards: one batch fetch or join — not staggered per-row requests.
- Filter and paginate at database level; minimize payload size.
- ComplianceDashboard pattern: collect IDs first, then `Promise.all` batch fetch.

## Frontend Invariants (Prevent Silent Breaks)

- Call `refreshUser()` after every `base44.auth.updateMe()` in the rider app.
- Onboarding phases: do not change `getOnboardingPhase()` order without a migration plan.
- Verification tasks: 0=identity, 1=bike, 2=owner — do not reorder indices.
- Rider UI copy: say "BodaSure Wallet" — not "SasaPay".
- Completed onboarding phases: read-only mode with `ReadOnlyBanner`.

## Backend Invariants

- Functions: `createClientFromRequest` → auth check → validate input → `asServiceRole` for admin/webhooks.
- Normalize phone to E.164 `254XXXXXXXXX` before SasaPay and Africa's Talking API calls.
- Coerce SasaPay `accountNumber` to string before Wallet entity write.

## File Hygiene

- Target ~200 lines per file; split orchestrators from presentational components.
- Business logic belongs in `src/lib/` — not duplicated across pages.

## When to Escalate to PM (Stop and Ask)

- Remove duplicate phone/ID blocks or weaken webhook verification.
- Change onboarding phase gates or KYC document types.
- Switch SMS or SasaPay to production environment.
- Schema changes without updating `src/ARCHITECTURE.md` and `src/FEATURE_CONTRACTS.md`.
